						               													<description>The god Kayros has summoned all the best thieves from every age to confront each other in a great tournament that will establish, once and for all, who is the greatest thief in each universe. To win, Robin Hood, Ars&amp;egrave;ne Lupin and the other thieves will have to travel through time and space to steal the world's most precious treasures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Kayros: A Game of Thieves&amp;quot; is a board game for 1-6 players (solo, 1v1, 2v2, 3v3, 2v2v2, or free-for-all).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts the game with a character who has his own abilities and characteristics.&amp;#10;Each turn the players draw 2 cards from the Main Deck (consisting of Tool and Event cards) and gain 1 coin.&amp;#10;On their turn, players can play cards from their hand to enhance their character and get in the way of their opponents. Some cards can be played on your opponent's turn, while others can only be played on your turn.&amp;#10;Coins can be used to trade with other players or to buy Silver and Gold Tools, cards that will greatly enhance your character!&amp;#10;The main purpose of the game is to steal the Treasures placed in the center of the table, but it is not the only way to win the game, in fact other factors contribute to the victory, including above all the Event cards which contain objectives that if completed, provide Victory Points.&amp;#10;The game ends when a player completes two sets of Treasures (a set is made up of three treasures of the same type or all of different types) and then the Victory Points are counted!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
